refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
public voidVector::resize intsize mixedvalue0
Resizes the vector. If it is enlarged, then the value parameter will be used to fill in the new slots. If it is made smaller, then the end values will be truncated.

  &reftitle.examples;



    Resizing a vector


<?php

use pht\Vector;

$vector = new Vector(1);
var_dump($vector);
$vector->resize(2, 1);
var_dump($vector);
$vector->resize(1, 2); // unused second arg
var_dump($vector);


    &example.outputs;


